## 13. Planned Engines

Engines are **optional, bounded subsystems** that attach to core lifecycle events. They must not alter assessment content or scoring without governance approval.

### Analytics Engine

**Purpose:** Understand product usage patterns to improve UX and reliability.

**Collects (subject to privacy policy):** session start, question progress milestones, completion, print, restart, errors — not answer values by default.

**Must not:** Exfiltrate identifiable spiritual assessment content without explicit informed consent.

---

### Feedback Engine

**Purpose:** Capture user feedback on question clarity, report usefulness, and technical issues.

**Collects:** Free text, optional question/report version reference, optional section ID — submitted voluntarily.

**Must not:** Auto-modify protected content based on feedback without human and domain review.

---

### Trend Engine

**Purpose:** Show the user their own progress across assessments over time.

**Outputs:** Section/overall deltas, trend direction, encouraging framing.

**Must not:** Compare users against each other; shame regression; hide methodological version changes.

---

### History Engine

**Purpose:** Persist and retrieve past assessment snapshots.

**Stores:** Timestamp, answers, report snapshot, content version, scoring version.

**Must not:** Mutate historical snapshots when rules change; must version and disclose.

---

### Action Engine

**Purpose:** Transform weak areas into structured, trackable action plans.

**Outputs:** Prioritized actions from low-scoring questions/sections; future: check-ins and completion tracking.

**Must not:** Replace Islamic tarbiyah with generic self-help; actions must trace to approved improvement content.

